      "rationale": "Model form assessment at MRL 5 requires justification of all modeling assumptions with sensitivity analysis. The Reynolds-averaged Navier-Stokes (RANS) SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on published benchmark comparisons for rotating machinery flows. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation with Zhang modifications) was selected based on literature review of 8 candidate models. Model form uncertainty was quantified by comparing NIH predictions from three turbulence models (SST k-ω, k-ε realizable, RSM) and two hemolysis correlations, yielding model form uncertainty of ±12% on NIH. Achieved Level 4 meets required Level 4.",
